TEACHER ROLE

I presented one new material today: Teen Boards to Emma. She was ready for it based on her work with Number Rods. Presentation went well - took about 15 minutes.

Rest of the time was observation and minimal intervention. Helped Noah find work when he couldn't decide (around 10:40). Reminded two kids to walk (not run) during transition time.

Spent about 20 minutes observing without interacting - just watching work cycles, noting what materials are being used, who needs what next.

