POSITIVE OBSERVATIONS

**Independence**: Most kids can now choose work, get it themselves, work independently, and return it without constant checking in. This is huge progress from September.

**Concentration**: Multiple kids working for 15-20+ minutes on one material. Work cycle is solidifying.

**Care of materials**: Generally good. Kids handle materials carefully, return them to proper places. 

**Peer learning**: Saw Emma show Sophia how to use the Brown Stair. Unprompted, just helpful. Love this.

---

MATH/LANGUAGE FOCUS (VISIT 2 SPECIFIC)

Math materials being used regularly. Number Rods, Spindle Boxes, and the new number line are all popular. Kids are building strong foundation in quantity and numeral recognition.

Language area is active. Sandpaper Letters being used daily. Movable Alphabet starting to be used by older kids for encoding. Reading prep is happening.

Need to remember: Montessori math and language happens throughout the day, not just with "math materials." Counting during snack, writing their names at sign-in, reading labels around room - all counts.

